quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  4,128,"And if a woman feareth from her husband refractoriness or estrangement, it shall be no blame on the twain if they effect between them a reconciliation; and reconciliation is better. And souls are engrained with greed. And if ye act kindly and fear Him, then verily Allah is ever of that which ye work Aware"
  4,129,"And ye are not able to deal evenly between the wives, even though ye long to do so, but incline not an extreme inclining so that ye may leave her as one ahanging. And if ye effect a reconciliation and fear Allah, then Allah is ever Forgiving, Merciful"
  4,130,"And if the twain must sunder, Allah shall render the twain independent out of His bounty, and Allah is ever Bountiful, Wise"
  4,131,"Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth. And assuredly We enjoined those who were vouchsafed the Book before you and yourselves: fear Allah, and if ye disbelieve then Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth; and Allah is ever Self-Sufficient, Praiseworthy"
  4,132,"And Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth, and sufficeth Allah as a Champion"
  4,133,"If He will, He will take you away, O mankind! and bring forward others; and over that Allah is ever Potent"
  4,134,"Whosoever seeketh the reward of this world, with Allah is the reward of this world and of the Hereafter; and Allah is ever Hearing, Beholding"